"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-07-South-African-laser-run-U19-world-champion-s-Olympic-dream-1vScO1nokRa-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Global Stringer  Copied  South African athlete Jaun-Pierre Van Den Berg became the U19 laser-run world champion in less than a year of starting the sport. He started laser-run for fun but then grew into a professional under the guidance of his coach. To achieve outstanding results, he maintains a high degree of self-discipline in his daily training, stays focused on his goals,\\u00a0and constantly challenges and exceeds his limits. Participating in the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics is his next goal. To realize this Olympic dream, he says he will give it his all.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"